4 SYNOPSIS:
5 The Public Service Commission regulates certain
6 utilities in the state. The commission is comprised of
7 three members who are elected at-large and serve terms
8 of four years.
9 This bill would increase the number of public
10 service commissioners so that a commissioner is elected
11 to serve each congressional district. The membership of
12 the commission would be phased in and staggered and
13 would set commissioners' terms at six years.
14 This bill would prohibit an increase in electric
15 retail base rates until June 1, 2029, and thereafter,
16 prohibit an electric utility from including costs
17 incurred by the utility and related to giving certain
18 grants, lobbying, or advertising for the utility, other
19 than advertising for public safety purposes approved by
20 the commissioners, from being included in the
21 determination of a schedule for rates or service
22 regulations.
23 This bill would create the position of Secretary
24 of Energy to serve as the administrative director of
25 the Public Service Commission. The Secretary of Energy
26 would be a cabinet member and be appointed by the
27 Governor.
28 This bill would also make nonsubstantive,
Page 1

This bill would also make nonsubstantive,
SB360 INTRODUCED
29 technical revisions to update the existing code
30 language to current style.
