33 A BILL
34 TO BE ENTITLED
35 AN ACT
36
37 Relating to the Public Service Commission; to establish
38 the Power to the People Act; to amend Sections 37-1-1, 37-1-3,
39 37-1-5, and 37-1-12, Code of Alabama 1975; to revise the
40 membership and terms of the public service commissioners; to
41 establish the Secretary of Energy as a cabinet member
42 appointed by the Governor and provide for the duties of the
43 secretary; to add Sections 37-1-81.1 and 37-1-81.2 to the Code
44 of Alabama 1975, to prohibit an increase in electric retail
45 base rates for a certain period and thereafter prohibit
46 electric utilities from including certain costs in the
47 calculation or determination of rates or service regulations;
48 to require the commission to hold a public meeting at least
49 annually; to amend Sections 17-14-2, 17-14-3, and 36-3-1, Code
50 of Alabama 1975, to make conforming changes; to repeal Section
51 37-1-9, Code of Alabama 1975, relating to public service
52 commissioners; and to make nonsubstantive, technical revisions
53 to update the existing code language to current style.
54 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
55 Section 1. This act shall be known and may be cited as
56 the Power to the People Act.
Page 2

the Power to the People Act.
